<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-475-579  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 475 579.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 24 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>German firm may buy half of Novatel. (Robert Bosch GmbH)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Alberta Government Telephones (divestment)NovAtel Corp. (management)Robert Bosch GmbH (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     DivestmentTelephone CompaniesCellular RadioTelephonesAcquisition.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GERMAN FIRM MAY BUY HALF OF NOVATEL CALGARY, ALBERTA, CANADA, 1990 JUL 19(NB) -- Alberta Government Telephones has been talking to Robert Bosch GmbHof Stuttgart, West Germany, about selling half of Novatel, its cellulartelephone manufacturing subsidiary.andM;The government-owned telephone company has been sole owner of Novatel sincebuying the half it did not already own from former partner Nova Corp. earlylast year.andM;John Burrows, chairman and chief executive of Novatel, told Newsbytes Boschis the most serious candidate to buy a half share in his company, althoughthe deal is not firm yet.andP;  &quot;I'm prepared to confirm that we have beennegotiating with Robert Bosch over the past year,&quot; he said.andP;  Novatel hastalked with Bosch &quot;not exclusively, but more seriously than any other,&quot;Burrows added.andM;AGT has made no secret of the fact that it wants a partner to help it providefinancial backing and other resources for Novatel.andP;  Bob Lidgren, a spokesmanfor AGT, said the company has intended to find a replacement partner eversince buying Nova out.andM;Burrows said negotiations are unlikely to last much longer.andP;  Quite soon, hesaid, &quot;whether we have a deal or whether we don't have a deal will becomeevident.&quot;andM;He would not confirm or deny reports in the Toronto newspaper The Globe andMail that Bosch is set to pay between C$150 million and C$180 million forhalf of Novatel.andP;  &quot;I have no idea where those figures came from,&quot; Burrowssaid.andP;  AGT paid Nova C$42.5 million for half of the company 18 months ago.andM;(Grant Buckler/19900719/Press Contact: Novatel, 403-295-4500; Bob Lidgren,AGT, 530-3975)</TEXT></DOC>